description:
In packages/mcp-server/src/constants.ts, the UPWARD_FEEDBACK_LABELS constant uses Record<string, string> but should use the UPWARD_FEEDBACK_KEYS for type safety.

Current (around line 74):
export const UPWARD_FEEDBACK_LABELS: Record<string, string> = {
  leadership_adaptability: "Leadership Adaptability",
  ...
};

Change to:
export type UpwardFeedbackKey = typeof UPWARD_FEEDBACK_KEYS[number];
export const UPWARD_FEEDBACK_LABELS: Record<UpwardFeedbackKey, string> = {
  leadership_adaptability: "Leadership Adaptability",
  ...
};

This ensures that if a key is added to UPWARD_FEEDBACK_KEYS, the labels must also be updated (TypeScript will flag the missing key at compile time).

Also export the UpwardFeedbackKey type for use elsewhere.
Run npx tsc --noEmit to verify.
